Since your API is available over a non-secure protocol (http), iOS will prevent any call to it, you need either to make it secure (https) or you can add exceptions for development purposes.

To add an exception for a specific domain, add the following in your App&#39;s info.plist:

```xml
&lt;key&gt;NSAppTransportSecurity&lt;/key&gt;
&lt;dict&gt;
  &lt;key&gt;NSAllowsArbitraryLoads&lt;/key&gt;
  &lt;false/&gt;
  &lt;key&gt;NSExceptionDomains&lt;/key&gt;
  &lt;dict&gt;
    &lt;key&gt;your-domain-here.com&lt;/key&gt;
    &lt;dict&gt;
      &lt;key&gt;NSIncludesSubdomains&lt;/key&gt;
      &lt;true/&gt;
      &lt;key&gt;NSExceptionAllowsInsecureHTTPLoads&lt;/key&gt;
      &lt;true/&gt;
    &lt;/dict&gt;
  &lt;/dict&gt;
&lt;/dict&gt;
```

Replace `your-domain-here.com` with your domain.

